# Pepper ROS Noetic Setup Guide

This repository contains the environment and instructions for running the **Pepper ROS** simulation within a Docker container.

## 1. Initial Setup

### Pull the base image
docker pull ghcr.io/00ducky13/pepper_stage1_ros:latest

### Build the image
docker build -t pepper_stage1_ros .

### Enable GUI support (Linux with X11)
xhost +local:docker

### Launch Container
docker run -it --rm \
    -e DISPLAY=$DISPLAY \
    -v /tmp/.X11-unix:/tmp/.X11-unix \
    -p 8080:8080 \
    pepper_stage1_ros

## 2. In the container

### Run the following commands inside the container

roscore &
export LIBGL_ALWAYS_SOFTWARE=1


### Launch the simulation (with GUI)
roslaunch pepper_gazebo_plugin pepper_gazebo_plugin_Y20.launch

### Launch the simulation (headless, view via http://localhost:8080)
roslaunch pepper_gazebo_plugin pepper_gazebo_plugin_Y20.launch gui:=false
